; A growing spiral — every iteration is a slightly longer line plus a fixed
; turn. Demonstrates:
;   - linear arithmetic on parameters (:LEN + 5 stays affine)
;   - that the abstract interpreter degrades gracefully: after the loop the
;     turtle has rotated and translated by amounts that depend on a
;     parameter, so the post-REPEAT hint is conservatively '?'.

TO SPIRAL :LEN :TURN :STEPS
  REPEAT :STEPS [
    FORWARD :LEN
    RIGHT :TURN
    MAKE "LEN :LEN + 5
  ]
END

SPIRAL 10 30 12
